{"parentUuid":"0e878087-10b2-40d7-b504-be9c089d44d8","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/nick/work/AutoIREE_plus_AI","sessionId":"570d49a3-e708-455a-9718-d5c8f1869562","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"main","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MfanhHsYnRDxB2oWJ19qEN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**AutoIREE Plus AI** is an automated compiler tuner for [IREE](https://github.com/openxla/iree) targeting RISC-V hardware. It finds optimal tiling configurations for ML model subgraphs to maximize performance.\n\n**Workflow** (4 stages):\n\n1. **`--init`** — Extract subgraph benchmarks from an ML model\n2. **`--profile`** — Measure baseline performance on hardware\n3. **`--tune` or `--ai-tune`** — Search for better tiling configs\n4. **`--export`** — Build the final optimized binary\n\n**Two tuning strategies:**\n\n- **Genetic Algorithm (`--tune`)** — Population-based iterative search (64 candidates, mutate/crossover, measure on hardware)\n- **AI Ranker (`--ai-tune`)** — A neural network (MLP) predicts the best tiling configs, only the top-K are actually measured on hardware. Keeps the result only if it beats the baseline.\n\nThe target hardware is RISC-V (with vector extensions), executed via QEMU or GDB-connected physical devices."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7435,"cache_read_input_tokens":8806,"output_tokens":308,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7435,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZKUX4aA864bDC1pgxX4W","type":"assistant","uuid":"f924f500-2219-4fab-8ce3-457a21e47d9c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:40:21.768Z"}
